      "text": [
        " شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ قَالَ «يَتَصَدَّقُ عَنْ كُلِّ يَوْمٍ بِمُدٍّ مِنْ حِنْطَةٍ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1951 - Abd al-Malik ibn Utbah al-Hashimi asked Abu al-Hasan (as) about an elderly man and an elderly woman who are too weak to fast during the Month of Ramadan.\nImam (as) said: \"They should give a mudd (a specific measure) of wheat as charity for each day.\""
        ]
      }
